accepts-transfers: Whether to accept players transferring from other servers
allow-flight: Whether survival mode players can fly using mods
allow-nether: Whether entities can use nether portals
broadcast-console-to-ops: Whether to broadcast server console output to online operators
broadcast-rcon-to-ops: Whether to broadcast rcon messages to online operators
bug-report-link: URL for report_bug server link, empty = not shown
difficulty: The default game difficulty mode for players
enable-code-of-conduct: Whether a code of conduct for the server will be read from the codeofconduct subfolder in the server.properties folder
enable-jmx-monitoring: Whether to expose an MBean with the Object name net.minecraft.server:type=Server and two attributes averageTickTime and tickTimes that expose the tick times in milliseconds
enable-query: Whether to enable query (provides information about the server)
enable-rcon: Whether to enable rcon (allows access to server console over the network)
enable-status: Whether the server will appear online in client server lists
enforce-secure-profile: Whether players without a Mojang signed public key will be kicked
enforce-whitelist: Whether changes to the whitelist will be enforced on reload of the file
entity-broadcast-range-percentage: The distance in percent that entities need to be to the player to be sent
force-gamemode: Whether players will be switched to the default gamemode on join
function-permission-level: The default permission level for functions
gamemode: The default game mode for players
generate-structures: Whether structure generation will be enabled
generator-settings: The settings to be used for world generation
hardcore: Whether created worlds will have hardcore mode
hide-online-players: Whether sending the player list on status requests will be disabled
initial-disabled-packs: The datapacks that will be disabled on world creation
initial-enabled-packs: The datapacks that will be enabled on world creation
level-name: The world name and directory path
level-seed: The seed for the generated world. Empty = random
level-type: The preset for the generated world
log-ips: Whether to log the IPs of incoming clients
management-server-enabled: Whether to enable the Minecraft Server Management Protocol
management-server-host: The host that the Minecraft Server Management Protocol is started on
management-server-port: The port that the Minecraft Server Management Protocol is started on
max-chained-neighbor-updates: The limit of consecutive neighbor updates before skipping additional ones. Negative = disable
max-players: The maximum amount of players that can be connected at once
max-tick-time: The maximum time, in ms, that a tick can take, before the server is considered crashed
max-world-size: The radius of the world until the world border
motd: The message displayed in the client's server list below the server name
network-compression-threshold: The size in bytes that a packet needs to be to get compressed
online-mode: Whether the server checks incoming players against the minecraft.net database
pause-when-empty-seconds: The time in seconds that the server is paused after there are no players online
player-idle-timeout: The time in minutes of idle before a player is kicked. 0 = disable
prevent-proxy-connections: Whether to prevent player connections if the ISP/AS from server is different to Mojang
query.port: The UDP port query listens on
rate-limit: The amount of packets a player can send before being kicked
rcon.port: The TCP port rcon listens on
region-file-compression: The algorithm used for compressing chunks
require-resource-pack: Whether the custom resource pack is mandatory to join the server
resource-pack: The download URL for the custom resource pack (max 250MiB)
resource-pack-id: The UUID of the custom resource pack, used to identify with clients
resource-pack-prompt: The prompt to players when a custom resource pack is required
resource-pack-sha1: The lowercase hex sha1 digest of the resource pack
server-ip: The IP address the server listens for connections on, empty = all available
server-port: The network port the server operates on
simulation-distance: The radius from any player that entities can be updated
spawn-protection: The side length of the spawn protected area
status-heartbeat-interval: The interval which the management server sends heartbeats to clients
sync-chunk-writes: Whether to use synchronous chunk writing
text-filtering-config: The configuration for the chat filter
text-filtering-version: The version of configuration used for text-filtering-config
use-native-transport: Whether to enable Linux packet optimization
view-distance: The radius of the chunks the server sends to clients
